You know, we're familiar with the parable that Jesus taught of the farmer who found treasure in his field.

00:47:26.401 --> 00:47:30.065
And in that day, people sometimes hid their treasures in field.

00:47:30.105 --> 00:47:38.855
And if a farmer was plowing the field and he suddenly discovered a jar filled with money or gold, he certainly would rejoice.

00:47:40.397 --> 00:47:41.618
There are great treasures.

00:47:42.658 --> 00:47:50.368
in the word of God, but we must dig for them as we read, as we meditate, as we pray, and when we find them, we do rejoice.

00:47:51.850 --> 00:47:57.177
If we read the word of God out of duty, that treasure may never be revealed to us.

00:47:58.319 --> 00:48:05.708
It is the expectant believer who delights to read and study day by day who will find the treasures within.

00:48:05.849 --> 00:48:10.034
Psalm 112 says, blessed is the man who fears the Lord

00:48:10.306 --> 00:48:13.511
and who finds great delight in his commands.

00:48:14.513 --> 00:48:14.833
Amen.

00:48:15.394 --> 00:48:17.377
Do you delight in God's word?

00:48:17.918 --> 00:48:23.227
Do you look forward to your time opening God's word and reading it and having that fellowship?

00:48:23.667 --> 00:48:31.259
Would you rather have God's word than food or your phone?

00:48:32.922 --> 00:48:35.346
There's a lot of competition between these two things, isn't there?

00:48:43.458 --> 00:48:46.103
We must listen to understand.

00:48:47.265 --> 00:48:48.688
We must rejoice.

00:48:48.748 --> 00:48:49.730
We must love the word.

00:48:50.652 --> 00:48:52.114
But lastly, we must live the word.

00:48:52.635 --> 00:48:53.397
We must obey it.

00:48:54.479 --> 00:49:06.642
Verse 13 says now on the second day, the heads of the fathers of the houses of all the people with the priests and the Levites were gathered to Ezra the scribe in order to understand the words and they found written in the law

00:49:06.882 --> 00:49:25.225
which the Lord had commanded by Moses, that the children of Israel should dwell in booths during the feast of the seventh month and that they should announce and proclaim in all the cities saying go out to the mountains and bring all of branches and of oil trees and myrtle branches and palm branches and make booths as it is written.

00:49:25.926 --> 00:49:35.378
And the people went out and they brought them and they made booths each one on the roof of his house or in their courtyards or in the courts of the house of God.

00:49:36.386 --> 00:49:40.591
or in the open square of the Watergate, or in the open square of the gate of Ephraim.

00:49:41.171 --> 00:49:46.497
So the whole assembly of those who had returned from captivity made booths and sat under them.

00:49:46.978 --> 00:49:52.143
For since the days of Joshua the son of none until that day, the children of Israel had not done so.

00:49:52.163 --> 00:49:54.386
And there was a very great gladness.

00:49:55.047 --> 00:49:59.752
And day by day, from the first day until the last, he read, Ezra read from the book of the law.

00:50:00.292 --> 00:50:02.014
And they kept the feast seven days.

00:50:02.515 --> 00:50:05.298
And on the eighth day there was a great assembly.

00:50:06.114 --> 00:50:13.324
They had understood the word, they had rejoiced in the word, and now reading it, they're understanding it, they're obeying it.

00:50:14.826 --> 00:50:19.573
And it says in verse 17, in their obedience to it, there was great gladness.

00:50:20.053 --> 00:50:24.980
As they understood, oh, this is what we need to do, we haven't been doing this in a while, we haven't been giving it attention.

00:50:25.361 --> 00:50:28.385
We're supposed to go out and build these booths.

00:50:29.206 --> 00:50:34.994
And so they did it, and they had joy in simply being obedient to what God had told them to do.

00:50:35.810 --> 00:50:39.013
You know, the day of atonement, we said, was celebrated on the 10th day.

00:50:40.995 --> 00:50:46.020
And the feast of tabernacles was five days later from the 15th to the 21st day.

00:50:46.801 --> 00:50:52.286
And so the leaders just had a few days to get the word out to all the people that this is what they were gonna do.

00:50:53.047 --> 00:50:58.752
And during the seven days of this feast, the Jews would live in the tents or the booths made of branches.

00:50:59.513 --> 00:51:01.915
And it was a time of reflection.

00:51:01.935 --> 00:51:04.818
They would reflect back on their time in the wilderness.

00:51:04.962 --> 00:51:07.164
they would reflect on their present situation.

00:51:07.205 --> 00:51:10.989
It was the harvest time and they were thankful to the Lord for his provision.

00:51:11.870 --> 00:51:15.814
It was a time of looking forward to the kingdom that God had promised them.

00:51:16.395 --> 00:51:22.922
It was a week long joyful festival focused on the goodness of God.

00:51:23.863 --> 00:51:33.554
And during this time, maybe where there was despondency or depression or anxiety, it was replaced with anticipation of hope and joy because

00:51:33.858 --> 00:51:35.400
You know, they still had a lot of work to do.

00:51:35.420 --> 00:51:44.250
There was still a lot of work in Jerusalem to do, but they had a new joy, and that joy of the Lord was giving them strength.

00:51:45.091 --> 00:51:50.798
Their celebration was not just for enjoyment, but for encouragement to keep going.

00:51:52.239 --> 00:51:55.163
It's not enough to just hear the word.

00:51:55.223 --> 00:51:59.548
James 1 tells us we must be not only hearers, but what?

00:52:00.189 --> 00:52:01.490
Doers of the word.

00:52:02.082 --> 00:52:05.688
And the Bible says that the joy of the Lord is our strength.

00:52:06.409 --> 00:52:08.613
The world's joy is temporary.

00:52:09.214 --> 00:52:19.591
But the joy that comes from knowing and rejoicing and obedience to the word is everlasting.

00:52:19.751 --> 00:52:21.194
It enriches our life.

00:52:22.596 --> 00:52:23.598
We've experienced it.

00:52:24.179 --> 00:52:26.162
We've experienced how the simple,

00:52:26.242 --> 00:52:32.508
Joy in the knowledge of God and what he's done for us makes our daily tasks, some of which seems so mundane.

00:52:33.109 --> 00:52:35.671
He gives us strength to do those tasks with joy.

00:52:36.953 --> 00:52:40.876
To the believer without joy, God's will is punishment.

00:52:41.857 --> 00:52:46.922
But to the believer happy in the Lord, the will of God is nourishment.

00:52:47.022 --> 00:52:50.906
It is hope, it's confidence, it's assurance, it's purpose.

00:52:51.987 --> 00:52:54.770
Matthew Henry writes, he says, holy joy,

00:52:55.138 --> 00:52:58.784
will be the oil to the wheels of obedience.

00:52:59.725 --> 00:53:07.777
And when our obedience to the word comes out of celebration, our service will be a delight and not a drudgery.

00:53:07.837 --> 00:53:08.859
How true that is.

00:53:11.203 --> 00:53:13.927
Did this celebration last?

00:53:14.007 --> 00:53:18.273
Did the revival of Ezra and Nehemiah last?

00:53:18.714 --> 00:53:23.922
Well, it did for a time until the people became careless

00:53:24.450 --> 00:53:27.413
and the leaders had to bring them back to the word.

00:53:28.694 --> 00:53:29.735
And it's the same in our day.

00:53:31.177 --> 00:53:36.883
There was a man who cynically asked a famous evangelist, Billy Sunday.

00:53:38.084 --> 00:53:40.266
He asked him, do revivals really last?

00:53:40.326 --> 00:53:41.747
In other words, are they really worthwhile?

00:53:43.169 --> 00:53:47.253
And Billy Sunday's response was perfect.

00:53:47.333 --> 00:53:50.416
He says, no, but neither does a bath.

00:53:50.436 --> 00:53:52.178
It's good to have them occasionally.

00:53:55.138 --> 00:54:01.786
Let us become people who listen to the word, who love the word, who live the word.

00:54:03.168 --> 00:54:14.261
From time to time in the history of the church, God's spirit has burdened God's people to pray, to search the scriptures and to confess their sins.

00:54:14.341 --> 00:54:22.371
And from these sincere spiritual exercises, he has seen fit to bring fresh life to his people.

00:54:23.352 --> 00:54:24.914
It happened in Nehemiah's day.

00:54:25.442 --> 00:54:27.946
And it can happen again today.

00:54:28.326 --> 00:54:31.031
And the question is, can it begin with you?

00:54:32.272 --> 00:54:38.842
We know this verse from Second Chronicles chapter seven, beginning in verse 13.

00:54:38.882 --> 00:54:54.386
It says, if my people who are called by my name will humble themselves and pray and seek my face and turn from their wicked ways, then I will hear from heaven and I will forgive their sin.

00:54:54.978 --> 00:54:57.000
and I will heal their land.

00:54:58.061 --> 00:54:59.823
And that begins with us.

00:54:59.883 --> 00:55:03.807
We want it to happen in our nation, but it needs to begin with us personally.

00:55:04.707 --> 00:55:04.968
Amen.

00:55:06.649 --> 00:55:17.920
Father, we thank you for this chapter in which we see the people, your people, responding to your word.

00:55:19.041 --> 00:55:23.986
And they responded with understanding, they responded with rejoicing,

00:55:24.706 --> 00:55:28.049
They responded with obeying.

00:55:28.089 --> 00:55:31.512
They listened to your word.

00:55:32.193 --> 00:55:33.434
They loved your word.

00:55:34.135 --> 00:55:35.456
They lived your word.

00:55:38.359 --> 00:55:40.221
Lord, would you do that new work in us?

00:55:41.522 --> 00:55:49.749
Would you bring us back to that place where we reverence this amazing book that you've given us?

00:55:52.152 --> 00:55:54.674
That we would recognize that it is

00:55:55.842 --> 00:55:56.923
a supernatural book.

00:55:58.105 --> 00:56:02.570
It is the amazing story of God's love for humankind.

00:56:03.511 --> 00:56:13.524
And all that he has done, first to create, then to provide, then to bring salvation to, and the glorious future he has for them.

00:56:13.964 --> 00:56:15.746
Lord, would we cherish this?

00:56:15.826 --> 00:56:20.592
And every time we open it, may we be people who rejoice at where we're gonna find in it.

00:56:21.253 --> 00:56:25.458
Lord, would you re-stoke that love for you and for

00:56:25.762 --> 00:56:27.584
the words that you have spoken to us.

00:56:29.467 --> 00:56:33.072
And Lord, those things that you show us may we be people who obey them.

00:56:33.913 --> 00:56:37.578
Not just people who talk about them, but may we be people who obey them.

00:56:38.619 --> 00:56:41.503
And may the joy of the Lord be our strength.

00:56:41.603 --> 00:56:47.331
May the tasks that you call us into in the highways and byways of our life.

00:56:48.212 --> 00:56:55.762
Lord, may they be done in that joyful and hopeful and confident expectation that you are with us.

00:56:56.002 --> 00:56:57.145
and that you will never leave us.

00:56:58.188 --> 00:57:00.373
Thank you, Lord, for everyone who's come here today.

00:57:00.494 --> 00:57:04.584
Lord, I pray that you will, you, by your Holy Spirit, will have been speaking to their heart.

00:57:06.128 --> 00:57:08.133
May they go with your blessing today.

00:57:08.174 --> 00:57:10.279
May you continue to speak to them in Jesus' name.

00:57:10.981 --> 00:57:11.442
Amen.
